<BLOCK1><TI>STATEMENT OF DEFENCE</TI>
<P>1. The Defendants deny the allegations set out in the Statement of Claim except as hereinafter admitted.</P>
<P>2. The Defendants admit that the mortgage in question came due on November 1, 2017 but state that they have always made all payments required under the mortgage and that the mortgage should be deemed to have been renewed on the same terms for a further period in accordance with the discussions between the Defendants and the Plaintiff.</P>
<P>3. The Defendants deny that the Plaintiff is entitled to late discharge fees or administration fees but state instead that the Defendants have always been willing to continue to make the monthly interest payments required under the mortgage and have continued to do so, and so no such fees should be payable.</P>
<P>4. The Defendants deny that the Plaintiff is entitled to possession of the properties as the Defendants are not in default of the mortgage and as the mortgage should be deemed to have been renewed.</P>
<P>5. The Defendants deny that any amount is outstanding for accrued interest and further deny that the Plaintiff is entitled to any legal costs given the fact that there has been no default.</P>
<P>6. The Defendants state that this claim should be dismissed as against them with costs.</P>
<P>January 11, 2019</P>
