<P><BOLD>THE MOTION IS FOR</BOLD> the following:</P>
<P>(a) summary judgment against the defendants for $632,840.36 plus a per diem of $238.36 in accordance with the Statement of Claim for payment under a mortgage made between the plaintiff and the defendants;</P>
<P>(b) possession of the lands as set-out in Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo;;</P>
<P>(c) interest at the rate of 14.5% per annum from November 1, 2018 to the date of payment or Judgment;</P>
<P>(d) post-judgment interest at the rate of 14.5% per annum;</P>
<P>(c) the costs of this action and motion on full indemnity basis; and</P>
<P>(d) such further and other relief as this Honourable Court may deem just.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE GROUNDS FOR THE MOTION ARE:</BOLD></P>
<P>(a) the defendant granted a mortgage to the plaintiff which mortgage is now in default and which has also come due;</P>
<P>(b) the plaintiff has brought a claim for payment and possession under the mortgage as against the defendants;</P>
<P>(c) the defendants served their defence on or about January 11, 2019;</P>
<P>(d) the statement of defence does not disclose any genuine issue requiring a trial;</P>
<P>(e) the <EM>Mortgages Act</EM>;</P>
<P>(h) Rules 1.04, 20.01(1), 20.04 and 64.04(14); and</P>
<P>(i) such further and other grounds as counsel may advise and this Court permits.</P>
