<P1><BOLD>Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; is a true copy of the renewal agreement dated October 27, 2017 and Marked as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; a true copy of the renewal agreement dated May 7, 2018.</BOLD></P1></P>
<P>6. When the mortgage was set to mature on May 1, 2018 the plaintiff demanded a full payout or steps would be taken to enforce same as set-out in a letter dated April 25, 2018. <BOLD>Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo; is a true copy of a letter from counsel for the plaintiff dated April 25, 2018 addressed to the defendants.</BOLD></P>
<P>7. Shortly after receiving the April 25, 2018 letter the defendants requested that the plaintiff grant another short term renewal in order that they be able to secure alternative financing in order to payout the plaintiff's mortgage in full. The plaintiff agreed to same provided that the defendants paid down the principle balance which they did. There is no obligation for the plaintiff to grant renewals. Once a mortgage has matured it is up to the lender to decide whether or not to grant a renewal.</P>
<P>8. The mortgage matured on November 1, 2018 at which time the full balance became due and payable in full. From my review of the file, the plaintiff contacted a representative for the defendants by email on July 11, 2018, July 26, 2018 and October 30, 2018 to inquire about the status of the defendant obtaining refinancing and that a discharge request has not been received yet. On September 17, 2018 counsel for plaintiff wrote to the defendants advising them that the plaintiff is not willing to renew the mortgage on maturity. The defendant was advised that they must payout the mortgage in full on or before November 1, 2018. <BOLD>Attached and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo; is a true copy of the letter dated September 17, 2018</BOLD>.</P>
<P>9. As of November 1, 2018 the mortgage balance had not been paid and is currently in default and such default has not been cured to date. At the request of counsel for the defendants, the plaintiff provided a statement effective February 28, 2019 advising as to how much is owed as of that day. As per the February 28, 2019 statement the amount owed is as follows:
