<P>10. The defendants are liable to pay these sums and subsequent interest at the rate of 14.5% per annum.</P>
<P>11. On November 29, 2018 a Notice of Sale Under Mortgage was commenced and all interested parties were notified that unless the sums were paid on or before January 9, 2019 that the plaintiffs advised that they would sell the property. Since that time, nothing has been paid towards the property. The defendants continue to reside in the property and it has not been listed to be sold yet.</P>
<P>12. I have reviewed the statement of defence and I do not believe that any viable defence has been raised by the defendants. The defendants are in default and the mortgage has become due and payable in full.</P>
<P>13. Section 16 of the mortgage addresses &ldquo;default of payment and issuing of notice of sale and statement of claim&rdquo;. Two of the consequences of the default of payment within that section include: (a) the calculation of administrative charges (which in this case amount to $3,000) and (b) liquidated damages from the mortgagor(s) a sum equal to the payment of three (3) months interest on the principal amount outstanding.</P>
<P>14. Based on the premise that the defendants continue to not make any payments on the mortgage the total amount owing with respect to interest as of November 1, 2018 equals $600,000 plus a per diem of $238.36 everyday thereafter. As of the motion scheduled for May 13, 2019 the amount due and owing for interest totals $46,003.48 (193 days).</P>
<P>15. I make this affidavit in support of a motion for summary judgment and for no other purpose.</P>
