<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF YAO JUN SITU</TI>
<P>I, Yao Jun Situ, of the City of Toronto, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am a Defendant herein and, as such, have knowledge of the matters herein after deposed to.</P>
<P>2. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a copy of the Statement of Defence that has been filed to this action. The facts set out in the Statement of Defence are true.</P>
<P>3. [location omitted] is a property owned by my brother and I. The property was purchased by my brother and I in 1993 to provide a place for our parents to reside. My mother, who is currently 85 years of age, continues to reside in this property. I purchased[location omitted]in 2009 and reside in that property with my family.</P>
<P>4. In May 2017, my brother and I took out a mortgage from the Plaintiff to be secured as against [location omitted]and[location omitted] for the purpose of paying property taxes that had come due with respect to a commercial property in which I have an interest at [location omitted] [location omitted]</P>
<P>5. The Mortgage of the Plaintiff was renewed and subsequently came due on November 1, 2018. All mortgage payments were made by myself during the currency of the mortgage.</P>
<P>6. I offered to renew the mortgage of the Plaintiff prior to its expiry, however, the Plaintiff refused. Commencing on or about November 1, 2018 the Plaintiff refused to accept any further mortgage payments and indicated that they sought a discharge of their mortgage.</P>
<P>7. Since that time I have actively been attempting to obtain replacement financing so that I may discharge the Plaintiff's mortgage. I have obtained replacement financing from the Equitable Trust Company in an amount which should be sufficient to discharge the Plaintiff's indebtedness.</P>
<P>8. Attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a copy of an email from Axess Law, the solicitors for myself and the Equitable Trust indicating the amounts that are available to discharge the mortgages as against 20 Latham Avenue and the collateral property which is [location omitted] [location omitted]</P>
<P>9. Attached hereto as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; to this my Affidavit is a copy of a discharge Statement that has been received from the Plaintiff. I dispute the entitlement of the Plaintiff to the amounts claimed for a three (3) month interest penalty and also for their administrative fees.</P>
<P>10. I was at all times willing to pay the monthly interest amounts and accordingly I contend that the Plaintiff is not entitled to a three (3) month interest penalty nor to their administrative fees nor to their legal fees herein.</P>
<P>11. I am willing to pay the principal amount outstanding, together with the interest to the date of payment in return for a discharge of the mortgage. The balance of the matter may be tried in the normal course. Alternatively, I am willing to proceed to Trial on all issues.</P>
<P>12. No Order for Possession should issue as I have been always willing to pay the Plaintiff's mortgage and neither my mother nor myself should not be inconvenienced by being forced to relocate given my willingness to pay the amounts properly outstanding.</P>
